==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hot
<hw>Hot</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <def><pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> of
<er>Hote</er>.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hot</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Hot
<hw>Hot</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos>
<adjf>Hotter</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Hottest</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</amorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>hot</ets>,
<ets>hat</ets>, AS. <ets>h⟦amac⟧t</ets>; akin to OS.
<ets>h⟦emac⟧t</ets>, D. <ets>heet</ets>, OHG. <ets>heiz</ets>, G.
<ets>heiss</ets>, Icel. <ets>heitr</ets>, Sw. <ets>het</ets>, Dan.
<ets>heed</ets>, <ets>hed</ets>; cf. Goth. <ets>heit⟦omac⟧</ets> fever,
<ets>hais</ets> torch. Cf. <er>Heat</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having
much sensible heat; exciting the feeling of warmth in a great degree;
very warm; -- opposed to <xex>cold</xex>, and exceeding <xex>warm</xex>
in degree; <as>as, a <ex>hot</ex> stove; <ex>hot</ex> water or
air.</as></def> ⟦ldquo⟧A <xex>hot</xex>venison pasty.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Characterized by heat, ardor, or animation; easily
excited; firely; vehement; passionate; violent; eager.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Achilles is impatient, <qex>hot</qex>, and revengeful.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There was mouthing in <qex>hot</qex> haste.</q>
<rj><qau>Byron.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Lustful; lewd; lecherous.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Acrid; biting; pungent; <as>as, <ex>hot</ex> as
mustard</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Hot bed</b></col> <fld>(Iron Manuf.)</fld>, <cd>an iron
platform in a rolling mill, on which hot bars, rails, etc., are laid to
cool.</cd> -- <col><b>Hot wall</b></col> <fld>(Gardening)</fld>, <cd>a
wall provided with flues for the conducting of heat, to hasten the
growth of fruit trees or the ripening of fruit.</cd> -- <col><b>Hot
well</b></col> <fld>(Condensing Engines)</fld>, <cd>a receptacle for the
hot water drawn from the condenser by the air pump. This water is
returned to the boiler, being drawn from the hot well by the feed
pump.</cd> -- <col><b>In hot water</b></col> (<mark>Fig.</mark>), <cd>in
trouble; in difficulties.</cd> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark></cs></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Burning; fiery; fervid; glowing; eager; animated;
brisk; vehement; precipitate; violent; furious; ardent; fervent;
impetuous; irascible; passionate; hasty; excitable.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hotbed</ent>⟦br⟧
